contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:34.288 --> 02:36.188
[girl sobbing]

02:36.657 --> 02:38.757
Oh, Aaron, what have you done?

02:49.370 --> 02:52.738
<i>♪ Hush, little baby
Don't say a word ♪</i>

02:52.740 --> 02:55.941
<i>♪ Mama's gonna buy you
A mockingbird ♪</i>

02:56.677 --> 02:59.745
<i>♪ And if that mockingbird
Don't die ♪</i>

03:01.215 --> 03:05.217
<i>♪ Mama sure going
To make you cry ♪</i>

03:07.454 --> 03:09.721
You photograph
extremely well, Angela.

03:09.723 --> 03:13.358
[sobbing] Please. No.

03:15.262 --> 03:18.297
I'll do whatever you want to do.
Don't hurt me.

03:18.666 --> 03:21.466
We tell them not to beg,
Aaron, and all they do is beg.

03:21.468 --> 03:24.436
We tell them not to plead,
and all they do is plead.

03:24.438 --> 03:26.705
Just a few simple rules.

03:27.575 --> 03:30.209
They always break the rules.

03:32.246 --> 03:35.480
It's really beautiful.
You're very talented.

03:37.818 --> 03:41.620
If you let me go,
I could help you make them.

03:41.922 --> 03:43.789
Do you really think so?

03:43.791 --> 03:46.625
Yeah. Yeah, we're gonna make so
much money selling them, too,

03:46.627 --> 03:47.926
and you can keep
all of the profits.

03:47.928 --> 03:51.463
I don't want to sell my dolls!
I love them.

03:51.465 --> 03:54.433
[crying] I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
I just wanted--

03:54.435 --> 03:56.902
Are you gonna tell me something
that I haven't heard before?

03:56.904 --> 03:58.303
Huh? Huh?

03:58.739 --> 04:00.639
Or are you gonna tell me
that you love me?

04:00.641 --> 04:01.740
What?

04:03.744 --> 04:04.910
[sobbing]

04:04.912 --> 04:06.812
Do you wanna play
a game with me?

04:06.814 --> 04:08.413
Sure. What kind of game?

04:08.849 --> 04:12.017
Rock, paper, scissors.
It's my favorite.

04:12.853 --> 04:14.486
I wasn't always good
at first.

04:16.423 --> 04:18.523
How? My hands...

04:20.861 --> 04:22.027
[whimpers]

04:22.029 --> 04:24.630
You look like
a paper girl to me.

04:26.033 --> 04:28.267
I can't tell you.
I'd lose.

04:29.036 --> 04:30.335
All right.

04:30.871 --> 04:32.437
[crying]

04:32.439 --> 04:33.538
Ready?

04:33.774 --> 04:39.278
One, two, three, go.

04:39.280 --> 04:40.846
[sobbing]

04:43.717 --> 04:45.684
Paper covers rock.

04:47.421 --> 04:49.688
You don't play fair.

04:49.957 --> 04:51.056
No.

04:52.493 --> 04:53.859
[wailing]

04:55.396 --> 04:57.296
- [blood splatters]
- [gasping]

04:57.598 --> 04:58.964
[choking]

05:00.701 --> 05:03.902
<i>♪ Hush, little baby ♪</i>

05:05.472 --> 05:08.807
<i>♪ Don't you cry ♪</i>

05:08.809 --> 05:11.310
[blood gushing]

05:12.713 --> 05:13.845
[exhales]

05:14.948 --> 05:19.785
I just wanna look
and fiddle a little bit.

05:20.954 --> 05:22.821
Fiddle and touch.

05:25.359 --> 05:26.491
And now...

05:26.493 --> 05:27.926
[breathing deeply]

05:27.928 --> 05:29.361
And now...

05:31.432 --> 05:33.765
And now you can't tell on me.

05:34.468 --> 05:36.368
Freeze! On the ground!

05:36.370 --> 05:39.371
- Take him down!
- Don't move! Don't move!

05:39.373 --> 05:40.872
Over here. White female down.

05:41.709 --> 05:42.808
All clear!

05:43.110 --> 05:44.976
You have the right
to remain silent.

05:44.978 --> 05:46.445
You fucking animal!

05:46.447 --> 05:48.980
- [grunting]
- Sir, calm down. Stop him.

05:49.650 --> 05:51.817
- Fucking monster!
- Doyle, relax.

05:51.819 --> 05:52.951
Fucking animal!

05:54.988 --> 05:56.588
Fucking psycho!

05:59.426 --> 06:00.992
You broke my mask.

06:01.662 --> 06:03.362
Aaron's gonna be so mad.

06:03.364 --> 06:04.596
[officer] Get her down.

06:04.598 --> 06:07.532
- Aaron? Aaron who?
- No. No, no, no! No!

06:07.534 --> 06:08.967
[gavel banging]

06:08.969 --> 06:10.869
We have done a thorough search

06:10.871 --> 06:13.605
and have found
not one iota of evidence

06:13.607 --> 06:18.443
that there is a twin brother named
Aaron or any other such name.

06:18.445 --> 06:21.947
That's a bunch of medical mumbo jumbo.
He belongs in prison!

06:21.949 --> 06:24.649
- [crowd] Yeah!
- Having been adjudged criminally insane

06:24.651 --> 06:29.488
and hopelessly incapable of telling
reality from homicidal fantasy,

06:29.490 --> 06:32.124
you are hereby remanded
into the custody

06:32.126 --> 06:35.594
of the state hospital
for the criminally insane

06:35.596 --> 06:37.662
for the duration
of your natural life.

06:37.664 --> 06:38.864
[crowd murmuring]

06:38.866 --> 06:40.132
- Order.
- I'll be waiting for you

06:40.134 --> 06:42.000
when you get out, asshole.

06:42.002 --> 06:44.536
- You sick bastard.
- Order in the court!

06:44.772 --> 06:45.937
Better watch out.

06:46.540 --> 06:48.407
You get out,
I'll be standing right there.

06:52.513 --> 06:53.879
[chains rattling]

06:57.017 --> 06:58.116
[lock buzzes]

06:58.852 --> 07:00.185
[grunting]

07:04.591 --> 07:06.925
- You're hurting me!
- Shut the fuck up!

07:06.927 --> 07:09.728
I said you're hurting me.

07:09.897 --> 07:11.730
- Told you this is a bad idea.
- [squelches]

07:11.732 --> 07:13.532
[screaming]

07:17.871 --> 07:19.137
[powering up]

07:20.007 --> 07:21.706
[electricity buzzing]

07:23.477 --> 07:25.577
[orderly screaming]

07:31.018 --> 07:34.085
Did you do this,
or did your imaginary twin do this?

07:38.459 --> 07:39.558
Peter?

07:41.495 --> 07:45.497
I don't have
an imaginary twin.

07:47.468 --> 07:49.835
Good. You can hit him.

07:53.907 --> 07:55.207
[device powers up]

07:55.909 --> 07:57.209
[groaning]

08:04.852 --> 08:06.518
[panting]

08:10.724 --> 08:15.026
[Doyle] <i>You know, somewhere out there
are the families of his victims.</i>

08:15.696 --> 08:18.029
Probably grinding their teeth
right now just like me.

08:19.132 --> 08:20.699
He's a fucking psycho.

08:20.701 --> 08:22.701
He should never be released,
that's for sure.

08:23.203 --> 08:25.270
I feel your frustration,
Detective Doyle,

08:25.272 --> 08:28.840
but Peter and I have made great
progress over the last decade.

08:29.042 --> 08:32.910
I feel completely certain
that he is free of his demons.

08:33.746 --> 08:35.514
Wish I could believe you.

08:38.150 --> 08:41.253
Peter, are you sure
you feel safe?

08:41.655 --> 08:43.889
Thanks to you, Doctor,
I feel much stronger now.

08:44.825 --> 08:46.992
I'll look forward
to our video sessions.

08:46.994 --> 08:48.093
Me, too.

08:50.130 --> 08:52.297
I'm here for you
whenever you need me, okay?

08:52.633 --> 08:53.732
Thank you.

08:56.904 --> 08:59.037
Be happy and believe.

09:03.277 --> 09:05.010
Take care, Peter.

09:16.924 --> 09:20.058
You know, if he relapses,

09:20.661 --> 09:24.262
your career is gonna be as dead
as all those girls he killed.

09:57.030 --> 09:58.830
[door creaks]

11:08.201 --> 11:09.367
[gasps]

12:58.779 --> 13:02.847
What have I told you
about coming into this room,

13:02.849 --> 13:04.115
you little bastard?

13:04.117 --> 13:05.517
I'm sorry, Uncle Charles.

13:05.519 --> 13:06.818
Are you a girl?

13:08.288 --> 13:10.288
Only girls play with dolls.

13:10.957 --> 13:14.359
Only a little girl
would disobey me constantly.

13:14.361 --> 13:16.361
I just wanted
to see my mother.

13:17.063 --> 13:19.497
So, if you want to be
a little girl so badly...

13:19.499 --> 13:20.799
No.

13:21.201 --> 13:23.168
...I'm going to make you one.

13:23.170 --> 13:25.804
- No! No!
- Come here, you little shit-ass.

13:25.806 --> 13:27.305
- Come!
- Let go! Aaron!

13:27.307 --> 13:29.240
- Help me! Aaron!
- Stop it. Stop it!

13:30.010 --> 13:32.510
[echoing] Help me! Aaron!

13:38.084 --> 13:39.184
[door shuts]

13:40.887 --> 13:42.120
[muffled laughter]

13:44.124 --> 13:45.223
[man singing]

14:29.569 --> 14:31.636
[panting]

14:34.975 --> 14:36.574
[phone rings]

14:39.079 --> 14:40.144
Hello.

14:40.146 --> 14:42.113
<i>Oh, hello. It's Dr. Bauer.</i>

14:42.115 --> 14:45.416
Just checking to see how things
are getting along in the old house.

14:46.987 --> 14:48.286
Nothing out of the ordinary.

14:48.288 --> 14:51.522
<i>Also, wanted to make sure
you had set up your video log</i>

14:51.524 --> 14:53.925
and that everything
was working smoothly.

14:54.361 --> 14:57.462
Yes.
Yes, I'm feeling my feelings.

14:58.331 --> 14:59.564
I'm right where I should be.

15:00.333 --> 15:03.334
<i>That's good.
Any problems with Aaron?</i>

15:03.336 --> 15:06.337
How could there be?
He doesn't exist.

15:08.208 --> 15:10.942
<i>Exactly.
That's wonderful to hear.</i>

15:11.912 --> 15:13.344
Well, I'm here if you need me.

15:13.346 --> 15:15.346
You have my cell,
you have all my numbers.

15:15.348 --> 15:19.183
Call me day or night, please,
for anything.

15:20.320 --> 15:22.921
Thank you. Good-bye.

15:25.258 --> 15:26.357
[beeps]

15:29.429 --> 15:29.560
Peter's log. Day one.

15:34.634 --> 15:38.269
It's a shame, my uncle allowed
this magnificent house to...

15:41.107 --> 15:42.273
[inhales]

15:43.243 --> 15:46.144
He was a great man.
Very well-respected.

15:46.146 --> 15:47.478
[scraping]

15:57.557 --> 15:59.424
[thumping]

15:59.426 --> 16:01.092
[shuffling]

16:31.992 --> 16:33.591
[creaking]

16:42.168 --> 16:43.267
Uncle Charles!

16:43.670 --> 16:45.069
[whimpering]

16:45.071 --> 16:46.304
[rustling]

16:47.340 --> 16:48.473
[woman] <i> Do it.</i>

16:49.709 --> 16:51.209
[Peter] <i> I don't wanna touch it!</i>

16:54.581 --> 16:56.047
[panting]

17:18.104 --> 17:19.569
Monica Barfield?
That's me.

17:19.571 --> 17:21.472
Great. Give me one minute
and I'll show you around.

17:21.473 --> 17:22.573
Okay.

17:24.176 --> 17:25.742
Do you have any questions?

17:25.744 --> 17:28.112
Are the lease papers
ready for me to sign?

17:28.114 --> 17:30.081
Yes, dear.

17:30.083 --> 17:31.682
But there's something that I'm
legally obligated to share with you.

17:32.419 --> 17:34.052
This wasn't a meth house,
was it?

17:34.054 --> 17:36.287
Oh, no, nothing to do
with this particular house.

17:36.790 --> 17:38.456
Oh.

17:38.458 --> 17:41.109
- Would it have to do with the view?
- That's very perceptive of you.

17:41.110 --> 17:43.761
- However, I really need to
tell you-- -It doesn't matter.

17:44.364 --> 17:46.531
- Even still, I'm bound to--
- It's fine. Really.

17:46.533 --> 17:49.267
I'm tired of living out of my
luggage and anxious to get settled.

17:49.669 --> 17:51.335
Who do I make
the rent check out to?

17:52.338 --> 17:54.205
[Realtor] Love a woman
who knows what she wants.

18:04.284 --> 18:05.483
[camera clicks]

18:14.160 --> 18:16.227
[woman] <i> Peter.</i>
[gasps]

18:22.469 --> 18:24.302
<i>Peter.</i>

18:40.854 --> 18:42.620
[woman sobbing]

19:06.246 --> 19:08.146
[screaming]

19:08.915 --> 19:10.181
[yelps]

19:11.351 --> 19:12.617
[panting]

19:18.791 --> 19:19.924
[camera clicks]

19:23.630 --> 19:24.729
[sighs]

19:25.565 --> 19:26.931
Peter's log. Day two.

19:28.801 --> 19:30.401
Strange thing happened.

19:32.372 --> 19:35.673
I got locked in the closet
my uncle used to lock me in.

19:36.676 --> 19:39.844
<i>At first, I thought
that it was Aaron, but...</i>

19:41.881 --> 19:45.383
<i>I know I invented him.</i>

19:47.720 --> 19:51.389
So, I removed the door
so it wouldn't happen again.

20:01.734 --> 20:03.234
[thunder rumbling]
[gasps]

20:11.411 --> 20:12.610
<i>Help me.</i>

20:25.525 --> 20:26.991
[screaming]

20:26.993 --> 20:28.292
[whimpers]

20:29.796 --> 20:33.598
You're trespassing!
You have no right to be here!

20:34.300 --> 20:35.399
Now, go!

20:37.337 --> 20:39.537
- Hey.
- What do you want?

20:39.539 --> 20:40.905
I saw the way
you treated that vet.

20:41.341 --> 20:43.641
Yeah?
Mind your own business, pal.

20:43.643 --> 20:45.409
He deserves our respect.

20:45.411 --> 20:49.547
He deserves to get a kick in the ass.
Now, take a walk.

20:52.919 --> 20:54.852
I can't believe
that you'd do this.

20:56.456 --> 20:58.022
Yeah, Zoe,
you stop right there.

20:58.524 --> 21:01.626
- What?
- You forged my signature for a tattoo?

21:01.628 --> 21:03.628
No, Dad signed for it.

21:05.632 --> 21:07.498
[woman] Don't walk away from me.

21:12.405 --> 21:16.440
Damn it. You got a hummingbird tattoo.
And did you know about this?

21:16.876 --> 21:19.377
I don't know.
Maybe. So what?

21:19.679 --> 21:22.880
"So what?" You're supposed to
be a good influence for her.

21:22.882 --> 21:25.683
She's not gonna listen to me,
especially if I nag her like you.

21:25.685 --> 21:27.918
Oh.

21:27.920 --> 21:30.288
Well, I suppose I should just let her do
anything she wants just like your father.

21:31.457 --> 21:33.057
[man] All right.
I'm gonna go wait in the car.

21:33.760 --> 21:35.359
Thanks for nothing,
Christopher.

21:37.864 --> 21:39.697
[scoffs] I give up.

22:24.811 --> 22:26.711
Peter's log. Day three.

22:27.613 --> 22:30.915
Spent the day running errands.
Groceries.

22:34.654 --> 22:36.020
I forgot the milk.

22:37.056 --> 22:39.357
[woman]
<i>You forgot something else.</i>

22:40.927 --> 22:41.992
[inhales]

22:42.628 --> 22:44.662
No. Not real.

22:44.664 --> 22:46.430
[woman] <i>That young girl...</i>
Phantom.

22:46.899 --> 22:48.399
<i>...with her family.</i>

22:49.836 --> 22:51.135
I didn't do anything.

22:52.105 --> 22:56.374
<i>She's so pretty. So young.</i>

22:57.643 --> 22:59.510
<i>Did he see her, too?</i>
No.

23:00.513 --> 23:05.549
He's not real. Aaron is not real.
Dr. Bauer said so.

23:16.028 --> 23:17.561
[knocking]

23:21.100 --> 23:22.800
Yes?

23:22.802 --> 23:26.003
Uh, my name is Monica Barfield.
I'm your new neighbor.

23:26.572 --> 23:28.839
I just moved in across
the street-- Oh!

23:29.909 --> 23:33.144
I am such a...
I'm such a klutz.

23:36.749 --> 23:40.084
I'll take this back.
You don't wanna eat it after...

23:41.521 --> 23:43.654
- Not that your floor is dirty--
- What do you want?

23:45.658 --> 23:46.757
Nothing. Just...

23:47.860 --> 23:49.026
Nothing?

23:49.162 --> 23:51.162
Did I say my name
is Monica Barfield?

23:53.166 --> 23:55.966
Okay. That makes me
an airhead and a klutz.

23:56.803 --> 23:57.902
[chuckles]

23:57.904 --> 24:00.871
These really would be happier
in the fridge.

24:01.707 --> 24:04.909
The kitchen...
It's this way? Yeah.

24:08.748 --> 24:11.148
My mother always said I was
like a bull in a china shop.

24:14.687 --> 24:15.886
I know who you are.

24:16.722 --> 24:18.956
I'm Monica Barfield,
your new neighbor.

24:24.630 --> 24:25.730
I know who you are.

24:25.731 --> 24:26.831
- Did I leave something out?
- You and I both know.

24:29.702 --> 24:32.203
- Who?
- She sent you to check up on me.

24:32.205 --> 24:33.504
Afraid not.

24:33.840 --> 24:35.873
You are not
who you say you are.

24:36.809 --> 24:38.242
Let's call Dr. Bauer
and ask her.

24:38.244 --> 24:40.778
No. Okay, okay, okay.
You got me.

24:44.083 --> 24:45.483
I'm a writer.

24:45.918 --> 24:47.718
You should leave now.

24:47.720 --> 24:50.488
No, but I wanna tell your story.
I have no story to tell.

24:50.490 --> 24:52.890
No. I wanna tell your story
from your point of view.

24:52.892 --> 24:56.494
To share your pain and torment
with those who have condemned you.

24:56.496 --> 24:58.128
Not interested.

24:58.130 --> 24:59.964
You would have the final approval
of every word in the book.

25:00.800 --> 25:02.233
Will you at least
think about it, sir?

25:02.235 --> 25:03.968
Think about all the people
it will help.

25:05.872 --> 25:07.071
[sighs]

25:08.641 --> 25:09.807
Thank you, Mr. Harris.

25:12.512 --> 25:15.112
How about, if you change your
mind and your answer is yes,

25:15.815 --> 25:17.548
all you have to do is

25:18.117 --> 25:20.618
place your broom on the
opposite side of the front door.

25:21.120 --> 25:22.286
That'll be our signal.

25:25.224 --> 25:26.524
Good night.

25:30.763 --> 25:31.862
[latch clicks]

25:33.633 --> 25:34.999
[voices whispering]

25:41.707 --> 25:43.073
[muffled screams]

25:45.545 --> 25:47.011
What the hell
are you playing at?

25:47.880 --> 25:50.047
I'm calling the police.
Who the hell--

25:50.049 --> 25:51.849
I am the police, goddamn it.

25:54.253 --> 25:57.555
Don't you know who that is?
Bringing cupcakes over there.

25:57.557 --> 25:59.924
I do. He's a serial killer.

26:00.726 --> 26:03.561
Uh-huh? Yeah, well,
then you must have a death wish.

26:04.597 --> 26:06.630
I'm a writer, a journalist.

26:06.632 --> 26:08.732
[laughs]
I'm gonna get his story.

26:09.168 --> 26:12.736
Yeah. Yeah.
And I'm Buddy Ebsen, okay?

26:13.205 --> 26:16.240
You ain't no goddamn journalist.
I know your Realtor.

26:16.809 --> 26:18.309
She told me all about you.

26:18.811 --> 26:20.044
Said you were...

26:21.280 --> 26:24.815
unfazed by
your infamous neighbor.

26:26.085 --> 26:29.353
You never published an article in
your whole fucking life or mine.

26:29.355 --> 26:31.255
All right? Monica Barfield?

26:31.257 --> 26:33.691
You ain't no journalist.
You don't even exist.

26:36.162 --> 26:38.162
Well, too bad,

26:38.965 --> 26:40.664
Detective Dechert.

26:40.666 --> 26:42.166
Who the fuck are you?

26:44.136 --> 26:45.736
I look just like her,
don't I?

26:49.075 --> 26:51.275
But you were too late
to save her.

26:51.777 --> 26:53.377
Peter's last victim?

26:54.914 --> 26:56.213
No way. This can't be.

26:56.616 --> 26:58.882
- My sister.
- Jesus.

26:59.952 --> 27:03.120
And you're officially retired.
You're not even a cop anymore.

27:03.122 --> 27:04.922
You're just Doyle.

27:05.324 --> 27:08.125
You know what, kiddo?

27:09.128 --> 27:11.929
I'll take my badge
to my grave, all right?

27:12.231 --> 27:14.898
You better have something to drink
around here. We got to chitchat.

27:17.403 --> 27:18.936
I have whiskey.

27:18.938 --> 27:20.270
Good.

27:20.272 --> 27:22.940
Why don't you get it out.
I might drink the whole bottle.

27:24.977 --> 27:27.945
I got two questions
for you, missy.

27:29.649 --> 27:30.748
Fire away.

27:32.818 --> 27:35.853
You think that murdering little
piece of shit really got cured?

27:35.855 --> 27:37.021
[pouring]

